From: Deragabu Agent <deragabu@localhost>
Date: Thu, 01 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/6] cmake: make SUNSHINE_TRAY respect SUNSHINE_ENABLE_TRAY option

constants.cmake unconditionally sets SUNSHINE_TRAY=1 via plain set(),
which overrides any -DSUNSHINE_ENABLE_TRAY=OFF passed on the cmake
command line. Wrap it in an if() so the option is respected on macOS.

---
 cmake/prep/constants.cmake | 6 +++++-
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/cmake/prep/constants.cmake b/cmake/prep/constants.cmake
index b80be1e3..ff6e980d 100644
--- a/cmake/prep/constants.cmake
+++ b/cmake/prep/constants.cmake
@@ -2,4 +2,8 @@
 set(SUNSHINE_SOURCE_ASSETS_DIR "${CMAKE_SOURCE_DIR}/src_assets")

 # enable system tray, we will disable this later if we cannot find the required package config on linux
-set(SUNSHINE_TRAY 1)
+if(SUNSHINE_ENABLE_TRAY)
+  set(SUNSHINE_TRAY 1)
+else()
+  set(SUNSHINE_TRAY 0)
+endif()
